    {
      "num": 5,
      "text": "An organization where executives 'shoot the messenger' by punishing those who bring bad news tends to see an increase in which element of the Fraud Triangle?",
      "tag": "Organizational Culture",
      "options": [
        "A. Opportunity, through reduced effective oversight",
        "B. Rationalization, as employees justify concealing problems",
        "C. Pressure, by creating a hostile work environment",
        "D. Capability, by selecting less qualified employees"
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "When honest reporting is punished, employees easily rationalize concealing problems—believing it is necessary for survival in the organization. (CFE Fraud Examiners Manual)",
